	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>blargg</b> [ Fri Dec 13, 2013 1:23 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Build GBA SP headphone adapter</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A charger cable might not connect the headphone out pins and thus have nothing to solder to. Looking at the <a href="http://pinoutsguide.com/Game/gameboy_speakers_pinout.shtml" class="postlink">pinout</a>, you have to connect headphone detect or it won't disable the internal speaker and output anything. Regarding quality, if you get a cheap cord from any country it won't last.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
